This is the Perl distribution Text-Pipe-Translate.

INSTALLATION

Text-Pipe-Translate installation is straightforward. If your CPAN shell is
set up, you should just be able to do

    % cpan Text::Pipe::Translate

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

Text-Pipe-Translate documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc Text::Pipe::Translate

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

